Stop-word lists (src/stopwords/*.ts)

Sourced per-language from two upstreams:

  - Snowball — snowballstem/snowball-website (BSD-3-Clause), pinned to
    commit ea94bd3f at path `algorithms/<lang>/stop.txt`.
    (15 languages: danish, dutch, english, finnish, french, german,
    hungarian, indonesian, irish, italian, norwegian, portuguese,
    russian, spanish, swedish).
    Same project family as the stemmers above; lists are designed to
    pair with the matching Snowball stemmer.

  - stopwords-iso — https://github.com/stopwords-iso/stopwords-iso
    pinned to v0.4.0 (stopwords-iso.json)
    (10 languages: arabic, armenian, greek, hindi, lithuanian, nepali,
    romanian, serbian, tamil, turkish).
    License: MIT. Per-language lists are aggregated from multiple
    upstream sources by the stopwords-iso maintainers.

Snowball's English stop list (174 words) is the canonical reference
used by Lucene, Solr, lunr-languages, and others. It deliberately
excludes content words — see `scripts/fetch-stopwords.ts` for the
per-language source assignment.
